Foot & mouth disease, virus identification (02) 20010323.0577
[1
Date: Mon 26 Mar 2001 15:26:11 +0200
From: Gideon Brueckner <DVS@Nda.Agric.za>

[With reference to the 23 Mar 2001 posting entitled "Foot & mouth disease,
virus identification (02) 20010323.0577, we strongly object to the
second-to-last paragraph and the footnote alleging that the outbreak of FMD
in the UK originated from South Africa. These are unsubstantiated rumors to
which we have also formally objected to the Ministry of Agriculture
Fisheries and Food (who were not responsible for the rumors and have
reacted in a very responsible and scientific way to our objections).
We were also in the unfortunate situation in September 2000 to experience
an outbreak of FMD Virus Type O caused by swill obtained from a ship from
the East and fed to pigs. Before this incident South Africa was zoned free
from FMD without vaccination. It was the first time this virus was ever
diagnosed in South Africa. The last clinical case of the disease was
diagnosed on 23 Oct 2000. The outbreak has been well contained within the
original 15 km area of infection. South Africa has on its own immediately
stopped all exports from the risk area, KwaZulu-Natal Province. It is also
wrong to assume that foot and mouth disease is endemic to South Africa. The
disease in South Africa is only endemic within the Kruger National Park
bordering Mozambique and Zimbawe. Only the SAT FMD viruses are present in
carrier African buffalo.
Dr Gideon Brueckner
Director Veterinary Services
Private Bag X138
PRETORIA 0001
SOUTH AFRICA
Tel: +27 12 319 7679
Fax: +27 12 329 7218
<dvs@nda.agric.za>
